<法規內容>
  <條文>
    <條號>Article 1</條號>
    <條文內容><![CDATA[This Standard is prescribed in accordance with the provisions of Article 17 of the Act Governing Food Sanitation.]]></條文內容>
  </條文>
  <條文>
    <條號>Article 2</條號>
    <條文內容><![CDATA[The name of the chemical is indicated as nitrous oxide, dinitrogenmonoxide or nitrogen oxide; the formula of the chemical is indicated as N2O, and its molecular weight is 44.01.]]></條文內容>
  </條文>
  <條文>
    <條號>Article 3</條號>
    <條文內容><![CDATA[Nitrous oxide to be used in food shall meet the requirements according to the following standards and tests：
┌───────────┬──────────────────┐
│Item                  │Standards and tests                 │
├───────────┼──────────────────┤
│Assay	                │Not less than 97% (v/v)             │
├───────────┼──────────────────┤
│Description           │Colourless, odourless gas           │
├───────────┼──────────────────┤
│Solubility            │1 volume dissolves in 1.5 volumes of│
│                      │water (20℃, 760 mm Hg)             │
├───────────┼──────────────────┤
│Flame test            │A glowing splinter of wood in       │
│                      │contact with nitrous oxide bursts   │
│                      │into flame (distinction from        │
│                      │nitrogen).                          │
├───────────┼──────────────────┤
│Pyrogallol test       │Collect about 100 mL of the gas     │
│                      │under test in a 100-mL tube fitted  │
│                      │at the top with a stopcock. Open the│
│                      │stopcock, and quickly add a freshly │
│                      │prepared solution of 500 mg of      │
│                      │pyrogallol in 2 mL of water and a   │
│                      │freshly prepared solution of 12 g of│
│                      │potassium hydroxide in 8 mL of      │
│                      │water. Immediately close the        │
│                      │stopcock and mix. The gas is not    │
│                      │absorbed and the solution does not  │
│                      │become brown(distinction from       │
│                      │oxygen).                            │
├───────────┼──────────────────┤
│Carbon monoxide       │Not more than 10 μL/L              │
├───────────┼──────────────────┤
│Nitric oxide and      │Not more than 5 μL/L               │
│nitrogen dioxide      │                                    │
├───────────┼──────────────────┤
│Halogens and hydrogen │Not more than 5 μL/L               │
│sulfide               │                                    │
├───────────┼──────────────────┤
│Arsine and phosphine  │Pass 10.0 L at a rate of 1.0 L/min  │
│                      │through a glass tube packed with    │
│                      │lead acetate TS on cotton wool and a│
│                      │gas distribution head of the domed, │
│                      │sintered type, of porosity 100, into│
│                      │a tube of about 2.5 cm internal     │
│                      │diameter, containing 5 mL of Silver │
│                      │DDC/Quinoline TS, the domed head    │
│                      │being almost in contact with the    │
│                      │bottom of the tube. The colour of   │
│                      │the Silver DDC/Quinoline TS is not  │
│                      │changed.                            │
│                      │                                    │
│                      │Silver DDC/Quinoline TS: Dissolve 50│
│                      │mg of finely powdered silver nitrate│
│                      │in 100 mL of quinoline and add 0.2 g│
│                      │of silver diethyldithiocarbamate.   │
│                      │The reagent should be freshly       │
│                      │prepared.                           │
└───────────┴──────────────────┘]]></條文內容>
  </條文>
  <條文>
    <條號>Article 4</條號>
    <條文內容><![CDATA[This Standard shall be implemented from the date of promulgation.]]></條文內容>
  </條文>
